entries.angry_disable: You have some nerve attacking a Nym craft
entries.arrival_phase_1: pcontrast3 CorSec: < pcontrast1 The vessel is not where the distress becon reported, stand by while we scan. pcontrast3 >
entries.arrival_phase_2: pcontrast3 CorSec: < pcontrast1 The ship is on the move again, not sure why they would do this but go catch them, we want questions answered. pcontrast3 >
entries.attack_notify: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 Enemy craft detected on attack vector. pcontrast3 >
entries.attack_stopped: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 Enemy activity has stopped. pcontrast3 >
entries.capture_complete: pcontrast3 CorSec Command: < pcontrast1 Now that you have him, escort him out of the system and we can handle it from there. pcontrast3 >
entries.capture_phase_1: System assault has begun on the ship.
entries.capture_phase_2: Systems have been captured.  Life support systems are altered, the pilot should be unconscious.
entries.capture_started: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 Uploading sytem virus pcontrast3 >
entries.complete: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 Operation is complete, ship is underway to its new destination. pcontrast3 >
entries.escort_remaining: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 An escorting craft has been destroyed, %DI remain pcontrast3 >
entries.escort_wiped_out: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 All escorting craft have been destroyed pcontrast3 >
entries.failed_destroy: The target ship was destroyed, you have failed your mission.
entries.failed_escape: The freighter has escaped, you have failed in you mission.
entries.panic_1: Help! They're on to us! We're being attacked.
entries.panic_2: Hey! Pay attention! They're attacking us!
entries.panic_3: Hey! Pay attention! They're attacking us!
entries.panic_4: Hey! Pay attention! They're attacking us!
entries.panic_5: Hey! Pay attention! They're attacking us!
entries.quest_disable_d: Target the Enforcer's engine to disable.
entries.quest_escort_d: Escort the Enforcer out of the system.
entries.quest_recover_d: Pull up close to the target to begin the recovery process.
entries.recovery_success: The target ship is secured, operation successful.
entries.split_quest_alert: pcontrast3 CorSec command: < pcontrast1 Good work. Patrol the supply line in the Endor System for suspicious activity. We're expecting an attack. pcontrast3 >
entries.target_disabled: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 The target ship has been disabled, move into position to begin capture process pcontrast3 >
